@startuml architecturalknowledgedb-c4-context
title ArchitecturalKnowledgeDB - C4 Context

actor "Architecture maintainer" as Maintainer
actor "Coding agent / MCP client" as Agent
actor "Website reader / evaluator" as Reader
rectangle "AIaGMW\n(optional outer tool)" as AIaGMW
rectangle "ArchitecturalKnowledgeDB\nOuter Tool" as AKDB
rectangle "Tiny Tool Website + Atlas\nstatic projection" as Website
database "SQLite + FTS\nproject knowledge DB" as DB
folder "Normative architecture sources\nGit/docs, Git/UML, ADRs, gates, schemas" as Sources
folder "Registered source repositories" as Repos

Maintainer --> AKDB : import, search, check drift
Agent --> AKDB : MCP search/context/tools
AIaGMW --> AKDB : optional context/read import
Reader --> Website : discover usage, benefits, integrations
Sources --> AKDB : imported and reingested
Repos --> AKDB : read-only Git/source metadata
Sources --> Website : product facts + curated SAD-backed copy
AKDB --> DB : stores indexed knowledge
AKDB --> Maintainer : context packs, findings, provenance
AKDB --> Agent : authority-aware responses
Website --> Reader : AKDB Outer Tool page + Atlas node

note right of Sources
  Files remain authoritative.
  AKDB is a derived index and context service.
end note

note bottom of Website
  Website celebrates AKDB as a product surface,
  but it is a static projection, not runtime authority.
end note

@enduml
